><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-9JLNr5MITsg/Ucl0a8pWRfI/AAAAAAAAAL4/A4h0iQGyeU0/s1600/20130624_204453.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"320\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-9JLNr5MITsg/Ucl0a8pWRfI/AAAAAAAAAL4/A4h0iQGyeU0/s320/20130624_204453.jpg\" width=\"240\" /></a></div><br /><br />" nil nil "6e33334a74570d34b34c7f9c52c64a7c") (217 (20949 15560 740923) "http://christianheilmann.com/2013/06/25/mobile-solutions-day-firefox-ossupercharged-html5/" "Christian Heilmann: Mobile Solutions Day =?utf-8?Q?=E2=80=93?= Firefox OS:supercharged HTML5" "Chris Heilmann" "Tue, 25 Jun 2013 13:25:38 +0000" "<p>Yesterday I did a one-day round-trip to Frankfurt, Germany to speak at T-Mobile’s <a href=\"http://molutions.de/\">Mobile Solutions Day</a> about Firefox OS and what it means for app developers. The slides are <a href=\"http://icant.co.uk/talks/h5/dt-day.html\">available here</a> and I recorded a screencast with not-that-amazing-but-does-the-job audio <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yQ5aZr842mg\">here</a>.</p>
